CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 17, 1965, pg. 8 reads:"Initial Payment - Members of the 7000 Bennett Street Block Club have as their project, working to improve conditions in Homewood area and helping the Pittsburgh Branch NAACP. Last Thursday, when the group met at the home of President Ms. Juanita McCarter, it made its initial payment on a life membership in the NAACP.  Seated, left to right: Mrs. Jean Hayward, vice president; Mrs. Dolores Rollins, Mrs. Helen Stoner Robinson and Mrs. Jessie Patterson.  Standing: Mrs. Margaret Lowery, Mrs. Violet Simms and Atty. Byrd R. Brown, president of Pittsburgh Branch NAACP, accepting check from Mrs. McCarter; Mrs. Mildred Crawford, Mrs. Eva Miller and Mrs. Ellen J. Wilson. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of the 7000 Bennett Street Block Club  from left, seated: Jean Hayward, Dolores Rollins, Helen Stoner Robinson, and Jessie Patterson; standing: Margaret Lowery, Violet Simms, Atty. Byrd R. Brown, accepting check for NAACP from Juanita McCarter, Mildred Crawford, Eva Miller, and Ellen J. Wilson, gathered in yard at home of Juanita McCarter
